  "prompt": "How did the Google Chrome extensions disappeared? How can I get them back?",
  "response": "If your Google Chrome extensions have disappeared, here are some steps to troubleshoot and potentially recover them:\n\n1. Check if extensions are disabled\n- Open Chrome\n- Click the three-dot menu in the top right\n- Go to More Tools > Extensions\n- Enable any extensions that are turned off\n\n2. Verify Chrome sync is working\n- Click your profile icon\n- Check if sync is enabled\n- Ensure extensions are selected for syncing\n\n3. Restart Chrome\n- Close and reopen the browser\n- Sometimes this simple step can resolve extension issues\n\n4. Check for Chrome profile problems\n- Create a new Chrome profile\n- See if extensions are present in the new profile\n\n5. Reinstall extensions\n- Go to Chrome Web Store\n- Manually reinstall missing extensions\n\n6. Reset Chrome settings\n- Go to Settings\n- Click \"Advanced\"\n- Select \"Reset and clean up\"\n- Choose \"Restore settings to their original defaults\"\n\n7. Update Chrome\n- Ensure you're running the latest version\n- Go to About Chrome to check for updates\n\nIf none of these steps work, you might need to:\n- Uninstall and reinstall Chrome\n- Restore from a backup\n- Contact Chrome support",
